Merrill Lynch Capital Markets said itreceived a mandate from Industrial Equity Ltd (IEL) ofAustralia to arrange a letter of credit facility in support of100 mln dlrs of medium term notes and U.S. Commercial paper tobe sold in the U.S. Domestic market.    Merrill, which will be the dealer for the medium term notesand commercial paper, said this was the first facility of itskind.  Sumitomo Trust and Banking Co Ltd has agreed to providethe letter of credit.    The letter of credit has a five year term, with anevergreen feature allowing for extension at the support banks'option.    The notes and paper will be issued by IEL's Sydney-basedsubsidiary, IEL Finance Ltd.    The letter of credit will be underwritten by a group ofbanks who will be paid a 20 basis point facility fee and a 25basis point utilisation fee.    IEL itself is 51 pct owned by Brierley Investments Ltd ofNew Zealand, Merrill Lynch said. REUTER&#3;